text: Renko () is a former municipality in Kanta-Häme, Finland. In 2008, the municipality had a population of 2,378. Neighbouring municipalities were Hattula, Hämeenlinna, Janakkala, Loppi and Tammela. It was merged with Hämeenlinna in 2009. == Other websites == * Official website Category:Former municipalities of Finland
